[{"id":27077,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["optically active and adds one mole of bromine","racemic mixture and is neutral","racemic mixture and gives a gas with saturated <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>NaHCO</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math> solution","optically active alcohol and is neutrall"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>Propanal and methanal undergo aldol condensation reaction with sodium hydroxide. The&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#945;</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#946;</mi></math>-unsaturated compound undergo&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo></math>conjugated addition with cyanide ion gives a racemic&nbsp;mixture. The cyanide undergo acidic hydrolysis gives carboxylic acid.</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/33d03f19-6a80-4647-93c7-50794c9da9ca-f0247494-7702-4af8-a6cd-674327490731-image.png\" style=\"width: 615px; height: 465px;\" /></p><p>Carboxylic acid will give <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>CO</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;gas, with <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>NaHCO</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math> solution</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (31 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27043,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/Jb1i8gPBI3b9RLHtUroOUVQuLMmUyuXxfYpYgS8y-hc.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/hbvMxpU7opb3i7OsXWyTMe64AG7TsmP8NbzJClrBkYI.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/Qe6ILN-2w9hM8aAH0e-qOL0ZpN8PKtRMMo0Zi4xShkw.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/VqN2z68M0Yk-QArfF5QQMjMwVJcvf3AEMDp5dj9_mH4.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>"],"answer":0,"solution":"This is an example of Tollen's reaction i.e. multiple cross aldol followed by cross Cannizaro reaction\n\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/nbyyA0AaK03u0sRW-dYUT7L3n6G6SKARYh7WXFApZZ8.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (23 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27032,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/lCq6Mw5q8JPDqNYKyHisrrDNnAx4ofx2_UjVVX5L3pA.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/2o9CwKquyG0jDkjQNLEq3bzCV5kHVX6RR73Kwya29Fs.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/r-NTmFQogzdkCT9COLg0s4kZ8UpLrf5eYJlBrWPnpxo.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/tHhfQCia-ldpFFlGVn-w5ZL2wl5j-w-EiKKgnLE_z9k.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>"],"answer":1,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/fTcSchx5JTQqfUQoxhFdZAY5fekK-RqTkcENAIulG4Y.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (3 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27063,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>LiAlH</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>,</mo><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>NaOH</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>aq</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></msub><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>NH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>NH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>/</mo><mi>KOH</mi><mo> </mo><mi>ethylene</mi><mo> </mo><mi>glycol</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>LiAlH</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>,</mo><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>NaOH</mi><mtext>(alc) </mtext></msub><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>Zn</mi><mo>/</mo><mi>HCl</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>DIBAL</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>NaOH</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>aq</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>NH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>NH</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>/</mo><mi>KOH</mi><mo> </mo><mo> </mo><mi>ethylene</mi><mo> </mo><mi>glycol</mi></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>DIBAL</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>NaOH</mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>alc</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow></msub><mo>,</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>Zn</mi><mo>/</mo><mi>HCl</mi></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>Diisobutylaluminum hydride (DIBAL-H) is an organoaluminum reagent typically used for the reduction esters or nitriles to aldehydes. </p><p>In the second step intramolecular aldol condensation reaction takes place. Cyclization occurs if the α carbon atom and the second carbonyl carbon atom can bond to form a five- or six-membered ring.</p><p>The Clemmensen reduction is a reaction that is used to reduce aldehydes or ketones to alkanes using hydrochloric acid and zinc amalgam. In the same condition, alcohol converts to alkenes.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/3f811fdd-d017-402a-9d19-adbc42ba234d.png\" style=\"width: 671px; height: 410px;\"/></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (29 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27066,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/8c3ba512-92ea-48b2-962a-b4aa2447b91a.png\" style=\"width: 170px; height: 156px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/19e7f829-8200-484f-bbcd-454c9f67ef00.png\" style=\"width: 350px; height: 124px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/89ba1116-2c0b-4b32-abd5-ae6025645fff.png\" style=\"width: 180px; height: 117px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/28d07189-747b-469b-8309-a4ef5d6e4b4d.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 83px;\" /></p>"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>Intramolecular Aldol condensations happen when a single molecule contains two&nbsp;aldehyde/ketone groups. When the alpha carbon of one group attacks the other, the molecule attacks itself forming a ring structure. The reaction is shown below.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/339f8e83-8405-4d6a-a25c-16bfc14450dc.png\" style=\"width: 500px; height: 260px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (12 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27071,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["A-III, B-IV, C-I, D-II","A-III, B-IV, C-II, D-I","A-IV, B-I, C-II, D-III","A-II, B-IV, C-III, D&ndash;I"],"answer":1,"solution":"<blockquote><p>(A) Aldehydes give red precipitate with Fehling&#39;s solution.</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/867f40ec-83c6-4cbc-84e3-ef0f8165b49d.png\" style=\"width: 818px; height: 132px;\" /></p><p>(B) Phenols give violet colour with neutral ferric chloride solution</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/7230d7ee-131d-4d6c-ab80-ebbf3bcbd335.png\" style=\"width: 623px; height: 187px;\" /></p><p>(C) Primary amines give isocyanides with chloroform in the presence of alkali. This reaction known as carbylamine reaction.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/1761f839-a0be-4578-822a-ce0242066e1e.png\" style=\"width: 396px; height: 162px;\" /></p><p>(D)&nbsp;1-phenylethanol give haloform reaction with sodium hypochlorite. The products are benzoate and chloroform.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/98585194-5acc-40c2-bf38-686c77fbed6c.png\" style=\"width: 550px; height: 140px;\" /></p><p>&nbsp;</p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (08 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27017,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["Both Statement I and Statement II are true","Both Statement I and Statement II are false","Statement I is true but Statement II is false","Statement I is false but Statement II is true"],"answer":3,"solution":"In Statement-I, evaluating the structure of semicarbazide ($\\text{H}_2\\text{N}-\\text{NH}-\\text{C}(=\\text{O})-\\text{NH}_2$), the lone pair of electrons on the $-\\text{NH}_2$ group directly attached to the carbonyl carbon is delocalized due to resonance. The terminal $-\\text{NH}_2$ group of the hydrazine part is not involved in resonance with the carbonyl group, making it significantly more nucleophilic.<br><br>Therefore, the condensation reaction of acetaldehyde with semicarbazide under optimum pH occurs at the terminal $-\\text{NH}_2$ group to yield acetaldehyde semicarbazone:<br><br>$\\text{CH}_3\\text{CH}=\\text{O} + \\text{H}_2\\text{N}-\\text{NH}-\\text{C}(=\\text{O})-\\text{NH}_2 \\rightarrow \\text{CH}_3\\text{CH}=\\text{N}-\\text{NH}-\\text{C}(=\\text{O})-\\text{NH}_2 + \\text{H}_2\\text{O}$<br><br>The product provided in Statement-I indicates an attack by the less nucleophilic amide nitrogen to form $\\text{CH}_3\\text{CH}=\\text{N}-\\text{C}(=\\text{O})-\\text{NH}-\\text{NH}_2$, which is incorrect. Thus, Statement-I is false.<br><br>In Statement-II, the given molecule $\\text{Ph}-\\text{CH}(\\text{OH})(\\text{OCH}_3)$ is a hemiacetal. Hemiacetals are unstable in the presence of dilute aqueous acid and undergo rapid hydrolysis to regenerate the corresponding carbonyl compound and alcohol.<br><br>$\\text{Ph}-\\text{CH}(\\text{OH})(\\text{OCH}_3) \\xrightarrow{\\text{dil. H}^+} \\text{Ph}-\\text{CH}=\\text{O} + \\text{CH}_3\\text{OH}$<br><br>This hydrolysis reaction successfully generates benzaldehyde ($\\text{Ph}-\\text{CH}=\\text{O}$). Thus, Statement-II is true.<br><br>We conclude that Statement-I is false but Statement-II is true.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (05 April Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27034,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["But-2-yne","Butan-2-ol","Butan-2-one","Butan-1-al"],"answer":2,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/KF9fPf4ub9hv_CmI5JFDS_ra4R-RuXXKWtDJWuejftk.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (2 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27169,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["Friedel Craft&#39;s acylation","Reimer-Tieman reaction","Cannizaro reaction","Wurtz reaction"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p>&nbsp;In cannizaro&nbsp;reaction carbon-carbon bond not formed<br /><br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/0d3394de-ba06-48d6-8bf2-1c6b01ed98df-qwzxs.png\" style=\"width: 408px; height: 72px;\" /><br /><br /><strong>Friedel Craft&#39;s acylation</strong><br /><br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/7944bf65-c3d6-4a5d-abf3-7e5ebf1f1f5c-derww.png\" style=\"width: 378px; height: 48px;\" /></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/2d188171-6914-4885-aa88-26f7067924ff-pioo.png\" style=\"width: 452px; height: 146px;\" /></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/5f2032ab-08b8-4ce5-b1ad-53f6462edcdf-image.png\" style=\"width: 329px; height: 53px;\" /><br /><br /><strong>Reimer-Tieman reaction</strong><br /><br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/68fe5ebc-4b97-4a75-a662-3d73f4b2b43a-image.png\" style=\"width: 308px; height: 128px;\" /><br /><br /><strong>Wurtz reaction<br /><br />&nbsp;</strong><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/73a848db-224f-410c-811f-741f4077f7c7-image.png\" style=\"width: 261px; height: 49px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2014 (09 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":27074,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"No reaction with strong base or acid indicates presence of strong neutrality or non-reactive functional hroup with a single oxygen. No positive 2,4-DNP test indicates absence of carbonyl compound. Same compound formation upon hydrogenation indicates single double bond. Thus, it is an ether.<br /><br />As per the language of given question, the best possible isomeric structure is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Ph</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>CH</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>CH</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>CH</mi><mn>3</mn></msub></math>&nbsp;(cis and trans). So, the answer is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math>.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (01 Feb Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27153,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/cdb15b82-b351-4cfe-b38b-eb90d8160406-image.png\" style=\"width: 241px; height: 138px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/5e091af3-23ca-4810-9877-151bc8667b8e-image.png\" style=\"width: 292px; height: 138px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/6eef1a0c-0b91-4ffc-859e-4c123a96ec5e-image.png\" style=\"width: 212px; height: 100px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/f23cbe4a-70cb-4206-a23e-678e7415ccba-image.png\" style=\"width: 263px; height: 138px;\" /></p>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<p>This reaction is cross aldol condensation reaction.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/da48f456-4cbb-4aa6-9504-2e03ef7071cd-image.png\" style=\"width: 494px; height: 247px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (09 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27079,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/1abf944d-4159-41e3-81d2-d31b53245c8d-9895091_A.png\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 178px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/d6e817e8-b084-405f-bb6d-4759db10604b-9895091_B.png\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 198px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4feccff3-c4fa-4e3d-a257-d0d33a4e7cb3-9895091_C.png\" style=\"width: 250px; height: 185px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/815177cb-5aaa-4cb7-9040-c2c9c5b036bc-9895091_D.png\" style=\"width: 300px; height: 272px;\" />"],"answer":1,"solution":"Cyanide ion acts as a nucleophile and attacks the carbonyl group of the methyl ketone forming a cyanohydrin ion, which on attack by ethanol&nbsp;ion leads to formation of carboxyl group and on further hydrolysis forms an ester. The alkanide ion from the grignard reagent then attacks the carbonyl of ester twice to form a diol with two alcohol groups attached to a&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>3</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi></msup></math>&nbsp;carbon. The sequence of reactions are given below:<br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/e142ce2a-7456-464f-a2d9-ac5b65ce6987-9895091_S.png\" style=\"width: 500px; height: 587px;\" />","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (29 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27106,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/207b68f9-759a-4b7f-8d9c-eea0a5a658c6-image.png\" style=\"width: 295px; height: 92px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/b94c4958-1d16-456b-a06d-1c72fb0b180c-image.png\" style=\"width: 299px; height: 90px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/7e462272-e4a1-4c18-bab0-94b695b7978d-image.png\" style=\"width: 257px; height: 120px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/1d60cdb3-5b5a-4124-b9e7-77d92f7009ae-image.png\" style=\"width: 330px; height: 82px;\" />"],"answer":1,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ca363da2-3d02-43a8-a304-a9111f4bbd50-image.png\" style=\"width: 971px; height: 170px;\" />","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (27 Aug Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27018,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["$CH_2 = CH - \\overset{O}{\\underset{\\|}{C}} - OH$","$CH_3 - CH = CH - CH = O$","$O = C - OH, \\, CH_2 - OH$ (with C-C bond)","$CH_3 - \\overset{O}{\\underset{\\|}{C}} - OH$"],"answer":2,"solution":"Given the molar ratio of C, O, and H in compound $x$ is equal, the empirical formula is $CHO$.<br><br>Empirical mass $= 12 + 1 + 16 = 29$ g mol$^{-1}$.<br><br>Since the molar mass of $x$ is $58$ g mol$^{-1}$, the molecular formula is $(CHO)_2$ or $C_2H_2O_2$.<br><br>The structure of $x$ is glyoxal, $OHC-CHO$.<br><br>Treatment of glyoxal with $50\\%$ KOH under reflux results in an intramolecular Cannizzaro reaction. One aldehyde group is oxidized to a carboxylate ion, and the other is reduced to a primary alcohol.<br><br>$OHC-CHO \\xrightarrow{50\\% \\text{ KOH}} HOCH_2-COO^{-}K^{+}$<br><br>Subsequent acidification yields glycolic acid ($y$).<br><br>$HOCH_2-COO^{-}K^{+} \\xrightarrow{H^{+}} HOCH_2-COOH$<br><br>The structure of $y$ is $HO-CH_2-COOH$.<br><br>Answer: $O = C - OH, \\, CH_2 - OH$ (with C-C bond)","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (02 April Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27042,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["(A)-(I), (B)-(IV), (C)-(III), (D)-(II)","(A)-(III), (B)-(II), (C)-(I), (D)-(IV)","(A)-(III), (B)-(IV), (C)-(I), (D)-(II)","(A)-(II), (B)-(III), (C)-(I), (D)-(IV)"],"answer":2,"solution":"Ozonolysis product\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/7p3hueXp5Gh2M62UqhmWRgBudUR6pSLY05U64Ms5ALs.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (23 Jan Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27110,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/7ca47d7c-e5d1-4a54-8aeb-54573a3f3081-image.png\" style=\"width: 161px; height: 114px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/1e146739-666f-444b-8d28-8366dde02716-image.png\" style=\"width: 167px; height: 119px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/69e40b18-5424-49d1-a8e8-476e55d8079f-image.png\" style=\"width: 176px; height: 114px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/f85c36e6-f048-4198-ac76-923e2ebdf4e6-image.png\" style=\"width: 190px; height: 116px;\" />"],"answer":3,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/7be6569c-55a8-4189-b479-82571dc5f076-image.png\" style=\"width: 538px; height: 389px;\" />","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (25 Jul Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27083,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/d3291e78-f0f2-49d9-a557-7d60aba9b9c4-9893925_!.PNG\" style=\"width: 227px; height: 150px;\" />","<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/0bf47ae7-6f61-4744-ba5b-c186e8532b55-9893925_2.PNG\" style=\"width: 231px; height: 153px;\" />","<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/d6e65e46-e709-4016-8228-554ef9248552-9893925_3.PNG\" style=\"width: 198px; height: 153px;\" />","<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/68a46b24-2d7d-4b8d-baf1-5d969c10582a-9893925_4.PNG\" style=\"width: 192px; height: 150px;\" />"],"answer":1,"solution":"<p>Ketonic part of the reactant reacts with sodium cyanide to give cyanohydrin and it cinverts to carboxylic acid on hydrolysis. The carboxylic acid part undergoes esterification reaction in the presence of ethyl alcohol in acidic medium. The ester part convert to tertiary alcohol with Grignard reagent.</p><p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/3544765e-b911-44e8-a52a-2015ee80e570-9893925_5.PNG\" style=\"width: 693px; height: 280px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (24 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27145,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/08e04a90-d516-4659-9a50-e2070164c0c4-image.png\" style=\"width: 146px; height: 159px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/11ae65bb-4079-4d99-a03d-f55e87f9da85-image.png\" style=\"width: 153px; height: 158px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/cf6721a2-1e19-4332-abb5-585505f7d61e-image.png\" style=\"width: 152px; height: 137px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/e1d9b207-8dc3-4083-823a-1ec077a205dc-image.png\" style=\"width: 151px; height: 157px;\" /></p>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>Nitriles are selectively reduced by DIBAL-H to imines followed by hydrolysis to aldehydes. Similarly, esters are also reduced to aldehyde with DlBAL-H<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/3a143728-ef6f-4820-b7ec-7a976710259c-image.png\" style=\"width: 582px; height: 143px;\" /></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (12 Jan Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27048,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/VpNMzKqs4ld50A0oKVZufGLdpMQWao4r1JwuZHjdRc8.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ckFmj8JCY1Xpye6vnzMOsh_JffiqJLliIYuVtJxcjWQ.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/wen4N9cKSo8BNAKPZ6egUo4yqY2xo6CXroHRVRypB9A.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ehd12r0v8QMg-Bo49BOwAukBw3d8M19nSp_ORH5CVv8.original.fullsize.png\"><br>"],"answer":2,"solution":"This is Gattermann-Koch reaction\n<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/_ppSiU_ObomiTUytxJMqDNFqG5F1QAWL9ImIYDKj0hc.original.fullsize.png\"><br>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (09 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27166,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["Perkin reaction","Gatterman-Koch Formylation","Kolbe's reaction","Gattermann reaction"],"answer":3,"solution":"No Solution Available","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2014 (11 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":27049,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["(A)-(IV), (B)-(III), (C)-(I), (D)-(II)","(A)-(II), (B)-(III), (C)-(IV), (D)-(I)","(A)-(IV), (B)-(I), (C)-(II), (D)-(III)","(A)-(III), (B)-(I), (C)-(IV), (D)-(II)"],"answer":0,"solution":"(A) Bayer's test $\\rightarrow$ Unsaturation\n(B) Ceric ammonium nitrate test $\\rightarrow$ Alcoholic-OH group\n(C) Phthalein dye test $\\rightarrow$ Phenol\n(D) Schiff's test $\\rightarrow$ Aldehyde","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (08 Apr Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27031,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/Opp6EQctJCwCv-6eGLLaVo4wdU7FHrS9ySCE2aVqTwQ.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/vbNKArbi7zbrTzjHHPnG8iBKCcZR-dvucnxsn7UVOBk.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ywuHaVzSNPJZDQVIG8NpTyoAjY2oMY2CCpu8JeQPyiU.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/NBklXGttFDI6vZ7OsB0VkywpwM4TVY6CIGmxsmpeUS0.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/_pZwK3HqUG3lPDH04wFOI30qik_2A2ZGJ8Izlic_XwU.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/t8TJs5LYqscaDQGgLueDgZtnjzScKgKakFx_mZ1zJQw.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/JaBDOnwK2v2fzHqXDbISaEvzQligyp7JIDdkkhnHgBY.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/YGh_k0U5vYF4adu2hYCOl6VQlMxwmb0k7qrq-0XA1qg.original.fullsize.png\"/><br/>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2025 (4 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27139,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></math> and <math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></math>","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi></math> and <img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/fff49d77-9b04-420a-b810-19b1f5da5c13-image.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 125px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/9dde26d8-79ce-47fe-8874-0653126e8f95-image.png\" style=\"width: 150px; height: 87px;\" />and <img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/f1bcc9bf-4fa6-4c68-9098-156e20049dd5-image.png\" style=\"width: 150px; height: 96px;\" />","<math><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></math> and <img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/d451c673-b9e1-468c-9f19-71fb5e79bab7-image.png\" style=\"width: 150px; height: 92px;\" />"],"answer":1,"solution":"Given reaction is a Cross Cannizzaro Reaction, since there are no <math><mo>&#8733;</mo><mo>-</mo><mtext>H</mtext></math> present on the Carbonyl compound.<br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/24597ae1-61da-4413-bb1a-82f0f2d01e9d-0648df16-1751-42c3-8b8a-2f1fb4d1c7dc-image.png\" style=\"width: 600px; height: 139px;\" /><br />Mechanism<br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/54d9f051-7c0b-4f6d-969e-1f2ccb66a76b-image.png\" style=\"width: 700px; height: 139px;\" /><br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/aa63f9bc-0898-4f5c-a02f-4f64957fe3d2-image49.png\" />","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2019 (10 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27085,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<blockquote><p>Aldehydes and ketones undergo reaction with HCN to produce cyanohydrins. The reaction progresses very slowly by using pure hydrogen cyanide. Hence, base as a catalyst helps to speed up the reaction. This is an example of nucleophilic addition reaction.</p><p>here we are given racemic mixture of optically active compound. The attacking nucleophile can attack on carbonyl carbon from either side forming a new chiral carbon. So, in product there will be two chiral carbon but it is symmetrical. So, number of stereoisomers will be 3 only.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/935d4577-18df-4b04-9f7d-87cf4133bd34-image.png\" style=\"width: 294px; height: 130px;\" /></p></blockquote>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2022 (29 Jul Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27172,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["acids and alcohols","alkanes and alcohols","ketones and aldehydes","n-alkaens and branched alkanes"],"answer":2,"solution":"All aldehydes and ketones show reaction with Tollen's reagent and Fehling solutions, but ketones do not show this reaction.\nNote :- Benzaldehyde do not give reaction with Fehling solution.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2012 (26 May Online)","image":null},{"id":27165,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>6</mn></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>5</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></math>","<math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>6</mn></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>5</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></math>","<math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>6</mn></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>5</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub></math>","<math><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>6</mn></mrow></msub><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>5</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi></math>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Treatment of an alkylbenzene with potassium&nbsp;permanganate&nbsp;results in&nbsp;oxidation&nbsp;to give&nbsp;benzoic acid. The position directly adjacent to an aromatic group is called the &ldquo;benzylic&rdquo; position. The reaction only works if there is a hydrogen attached to the carbon.&nbsp;Hence, toluene, on oxidation with&nbsp;potassium&nbsp;permanganate, gives benzoic acid <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>)</mo></math>.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/27103a2d-7b05-4ed8-a001-a26b46377d96-image.png\" style=\"width: 253px; height: 130px;\" /></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Carboxylic acids reacts with thionyl&nbsp;chloride to form&nbsp;acid chlorides. Hence, benzoic acid, on reaction&nbsp;with thionyl chloride <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><msub><mi>SOCl</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>)</mo></math>,&nbsp;gives benzoyl chloride <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>)</mo></math>.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/db91dcf2-ba4c-43c5-bb9f-cd3b42c19e52-image.png\" style=\"width: 401px; height: 120px;\" /></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Next reaction is the Rosenmund reaction. It&nbsp;is a reaction where acid chlorides are converted into aldehydes by using hydrogen gas over palladium poisoned by barium sulfate. Hence, benzoyl chloride&nbsp;upon reduction with <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>/</mo><mi>Pd</mi></math>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>BaSO</mi><mn>4</mn></msub></math>, forms benzaldehyde <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mo>)</mo></math>.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/150989b7-1b49-435b-a590-0fb379076d3d-image.png\" style=\"width: 441px; height: 140px;\" /></p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/afb435e8-afe9-4367-b677-376f5419520a-image.png\" style=\"width: 528px; height: 180px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2015 (04 Apr)","image":null},{"id":27158,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><msub><mi>NaBH</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi>ii</mi></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mi>Raney</mi><mo>&#160;</mo><mi>Ni</mi><mo>/</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&#160;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi>iii</mi></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><msub><mi>LiAlH</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>ii</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>&#160;&#160;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>6</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi>ii</mi></mfenced><mi>DIBAL</mi><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mo>&#160;&#160;</mo><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi>iii</mi></mfenced><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>","<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">i</mi></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>6</mn></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi>ii</mi></mfenced><msub><mi>SnCl</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>/</mo><mi>HCl</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mi>iii</mi></mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#160;</mi><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>3</mn></msub><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mo>+</mo></msup></math>"],"answer":3,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c65747bf-cc3a-444c-98cd-61843da5c9f9-73aa6fe1-8722-4d3e-bae9-5d3495e1e00a-image.png\" style=\"width: 500px; height: 184px;\" /><br /><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/bc1c9749-f0d0-488b-9f4e-65087f8df51b-5f62b43d-f20e-496b-b139-64437a365b8b-image.png\" style=\"width: 500px; height: 158px;\" />","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2018 (15 Apr)","image":null},{"id":27021,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["A, C & E Only","B, D & E Only","A & C Only","A, B & C Only"],"answer":2,"solution":"In the haloform reaction:<br><b>(A)</b> Sodium hypochlorite reacts with KI in acidic medium to generate the active halogenating species, forming KOI (potassium iodite/hypoidite). TRUE.<br><b>(B)</b> KOI serves as an oxidizing agent (not reducing) in the reaction, converting methyl ketones to carboxylic acids. FALSE.<br><b>(C)</b> $α,β$-unsaturated methylketones possess the essential methyl ketone group ($CH_3CO-$) required for haloform reaction, allowing iodination and subsequent cleavage. TRUE.<br><b>(D)</b> Isopropyl alcohol $(CH_3)_2CHOH$ lacks a methyl ketone group, so it cannot undergo the haloform reaction. TRUE.<br><b>(E)</b> Formic acid has no methyl ketone functionality, preventing haloform test. FALSE.<br>Therefore, statements A and C are true.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2026 (23 January Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27067,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["A","B","C","D"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>The reaction of aldehydes and ketones with ammonia&nbsp;forms imine derivatives, also known as Schiff bases (compounds having a C=N function). Imines can undergo nucleophilic addition reaction with&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>KCN</mi></math>. Now, nitration takes place on benzene ring. Then amine group under acetylation reaction with acetic anhydride.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/a099decb-d24a-4dd8-9dab-24a62af96665.png\" style=\"width: 687px; height: 317px;\" /></p><p>Now, the carboxylic acid group undergo esterification reaction with ethyl alcohol in acidic medium. Now, the nitro groups present on benzene undergo reduction to amines with&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>/</mo><mi>Pd</mi></math>. Now, the amino groups undergo diazotization with nitrous acid. Then substitution of iodine takes place at diazonium groups upon reaction with&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>NaI</mi></math>.</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/db064a8f-e8d6-4418-89ed-f4d83a449b3f.png\" style=\"width: 888px; height: 388px;\" /></p><p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&#8756;</mo><mo>&#160;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>15</mn></math></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2023 (12 Apr Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27109,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/4703437e-1763-485e-82fd-2466871841b7-image.png\" style=\"width: 439px; height: 125px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/976e2ae7-e191-4215-9e1d-a776835b153e-image.png\" style=\"width: 565px; height: 164px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/f33f0b89-5b69-4221-b482-25ef6672f6b3-image.png\" style=\"width: 637px; height: 147px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/e4c0cba4-7ce8-4bd4-a384-dfebacb498de-image.png\" style=\"width: 514px; height: 116px;\" />"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p>It is Haloform reaction.&nbsp;The haloform reaction is the reaction of a methyl ketone with chlorine, bromine, or iodine in the presence of hydroxide ions to give a carboxylate ion and a haloform.&nbsp;</p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/0652cbe8-eee0-4553-a8bb-7b965fdcd9a5-image.png\" style=\"width: 650px; height: 157px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (26 Aug Shift 1)","image":null},{"id":27119,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/e0d32560-6a5e-4471-9937-5fc60d5a423d-1795b15d-e0c4-44ca-9869-47bb9a4f57e0-image.png\" style=\"width: 194px; height: 101px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/853c7267-3a3b-4f19-9fcc-9ffd2203a2e9-image.png\" style=\"width: 222px; height: 106px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/33a3eb87-51a9-4df2-be31-d7fdbce56446-image.png\" style=\"width: 294px; height: 144px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/e1dec7b7-3621-4fc6-b4ac-fbb3178e197f-image.png\" style=\"width: 222px; height: 97px;\" />"],"answer":0,"solution":"<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/ffc1392b-216f-4ed1-87ed-cd1831d5f4c0-image.png\" style=\"width: 445px; height: 677px;\" />","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2021 (26 Feb Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27160,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/087ff6e4-1297-47d9-a6f1-b136d4fad7f2-image.png\" style=\"width: 190px; height: 100px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/8406694b-7e6d-43e8-9fbe-49ae188e4596-image.png\" style=\"width: 170px; height: 115px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/553bb498-867d-4c74-8621-aefaf74310a0-image.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 124px;\" /></p>","<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/a6bce176-73a9-421d-8da3-e2188af5116a-image.png\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 118px;\" /></p>"],"answer":0,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/d05b9142-ea4d-47cb-b28a-0fb676073900-3-5-2022tdo.png\" style=\"width: 600px; height: 307px;\" /></p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2017 (09 Apr Online)","image":null},{"id":27130,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/3b0804bb-7694-423d-8321-f8d0fa6b2ad6-image.png\" style=\"width: 140px; height: 60px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/fe48149f-93ec-4327-87ee-ce5268ab842f-image.png\" style=\"width: 175px; height: 87px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/af148f8c-b0b8-418c-9942-2a9b871aece5-image.png\" style=\"width: 181px; height: 59px;\" />","<img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/c0929494-8598-4d3f-ae96-149122c0cbc4-image.png\" style=\"width: 170px; height: 61px;\" />"],"answer":2,"solution":"<p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/3a5e630e-15c4-4a9a-91d4-fd4dc4064cee-image.png\" style=\"width: 824px; height: 132px;\" /></p><p><img src=\"https://.app/pyq/jee_main/fa43f73b-2892-4024-867b-29726394bfb0-image.png\" style=\"width: 752px; height: 219px;\" />&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p>","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2020 (03 Sep Shift 2)","image":null},{"id":27178,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["propene","1-butene","2-butene","ethene"],"answer":2,"solution":"2-butene is symmetrical alkene\n$\\mathrm{CH}_3-\\mathrm{CH}=\\mathrm{CH}-\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\frac{\\mathrm{O}_3}{\\mathrm{Zn} / \\mathrm{H}_2 \\mathrm{O}} 2 \\cdot 2 \\cdot \\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CHO}$\nMolar mass of $\\mathrm{CH}_3 \\mathrm{CHO}$ is $44 \\mathrm{u}$.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2010","image":null},{"id":27045,"subject":"Chemistry","chapter":"Aldehydes and Ketones","question":"","options":["A-III, B-IV, C-I, D-II","A-I, B-II, C-III, D-IV","A-IV, B-I, C-II, D-III","A-II, B-III, C-IV, D-I"],"answer":3,"solution":"(A) $\\mathrm{Br}_2$ water test is test of unsaturation in which reddish orange colour of bromine water disappears.\n(B) Alcohols given Red colour with ceric ammonium nitrate.\n(C) Phenol gives Violet colour with natural ferric chloride.\n(D) Aldehyde & Ketone give Yellow/Orange/Red Colour compounds with 2, 4-DNP i.e., 2, 4-Dinitrophenyl hydrazine.","type":"mcq","source":"JEE Main 2024 (09 Apr Shift 2)","image":null}]